The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Sunday, April 18, 2004 				 Lakhs robbed at gunpoint
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Armed miscreants riding a motorcycle snatched Rs 3.57 lakh and cheques worth about Rs 16 lakh at gunpoint from two employees of Life Insurance Corporation (LIC) in Beleghata on Saturday.																								The incident took place around noon on Hemchandra Naskar Road, a stones throw from the Beleghata police station.																								Two LIC employees were on their way to a local bank to deposit the cash and the cheques when a two-wheeler stopped in front of them. The pillion-rider snatched the briefcase and the goons sped away before they could raise an alarm, police said.Cop killed																								Asit Bhattacharjee, an official of the Howrah district armed police, was killed by miscreants at Barrackpore, on the citys northern fringes. Bhattacharjee was stopped on his way by three men on Saturday morning. After a heated exchange of words, they hurled a bomb at him. Alerted by the explosion, residents caught one of the miscreants. Intruder held: Kailash Rai, 24, was arrested on Saturday on charges of forcing his way into a New Alipore house. 
